    <section class="card">
      <h2>Skill: Factorising Quadratics</h2>
      <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Turn <code>x² + bx + c</code> into <code>(x+p)(x+q)</code>.</p>
      <h3>Method</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Find two numbers that multiply to <code>c</code> and add to <code>b</code>.</li>
        <li>Write those numbers inside brackets with <code>x</code>.</li>
        <li>Check by expanding.</li>
      </ol>
      <h3>Worked Example</h3>
      <p>Factorise: <code>x² + 7x + 12</code></p>
      <p>Need numbers that multiply to 12 and add to 7 → <strong>3 and 4</strong>.</p>
      <p><code>x² + 7x + 12 = (x+3)(x+4)</code></p>
      <p class="mistake"><strong>Common mistake:</strong> signs wrong when c is negative.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h3>Quick Practice</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><code>x² + 9x + 20</code></li>
        <li><code>x² + x - 12</code></li>
        <li><code>x² - 5x + 6</code></li>
      </ol>
      <details>
        <summary>Show Answers</summary>
        <p>1) (x+4)(x+5) <br/>2) (x+4)(x-3) <br/>3) (x-2)(x-3)</p>
      </details>
    </section>
